21. Advantages of JavaScript
Interview Definition

JavaScript is a lightweight, fast, and versatile programming language used to create interactive web applications on both the client-side and server-side.

Simple Language

JavaScript makes websites alive and interactive.

Without JavaScript:

❌ Buttons don't work
❌ Forms don't validate
❌ Sliders don't move

With JavaScript:

✅ Button Click
✅ Login Validation
✅ Animations
✅ Games
✅ Chat Apps
Advantages
1. Runs in Browser (Client Side)

Example

alert("Welcome");

No server needed.

2. Runs on Server (Node.js)

JavaScript can also create backend APIs.

Example

const express = require("express");
3. Easy to Learn

Syntax is simple.

