22. What are Object Prototypes?
Interview Definition

A prototype is an object from which other objects inherit properties and methods.

Simple Meaning

Prototype means

Parent Object

Children automatically get its properties.

Real Life Example

Father

↓

Son

The son inherits

Height
Eye Color
Surname

Similarly

Objects inherit methods.

Example

let arr = [];

We never wrote

arr.push()

ourselves.

Still it works.

Why?

Because

Array

↓

Array.prototype

↓

push()
pop()
map()
filter()

JavaScript automatically finds push() in Array.prototype.

Hinglish

Prototype = Parent object jisse methods inherit hote hain.

23. What are Callbacks?
Interview Definition

A callback is a function passed as an argument to another function and executed later.

Simple Example
function greet(name){
    console.log("Hello " + name);
}

function process(callback){
    callback("Lucky");
}

process(greet);

Output

Hello Lucky
Real Life Analogy

You order Pizza.

Restaurant says

"Pizza ready hone ke baad hum call karenge."

That call is a callback.

Hinglish

Callback = Ek function jo kisi doosre function ke complete hone ke baad chalaya jata hai.

