25. What is Memoization?
Interview Definition

Memoization is an optimization technique that stores previously computed results and reuses them instead of recalculating.

Simple Example

Suppose

10 + 20

First time

Computer calculates.

Second time

Instead of calculating again

Computer says

Already stored.

Returns cached value.

Real Life Analogy

Calculator

25 × 25

Already solved yesterday.

Instead of solving again

You look at your notebook.

That's memoization.

Hinglish

Memoization =

Ek baar calculation karo aur future ke liye save kar lo.

26. What is Recursion?
Interview Definition

Recursion is a technique where a function calls itself until a base condition is reached.

Example

function count(n){

    if(n==0)
        return;

    console.log(n);

    count(n-1);

}

count(3);

Output

3
2
1

Function keeps calling itself.

Real Life Analogy

Mirror in front of another mirror.

Reflection

↓

Reflection

↓

Reflection

Until it stops.

Hinglish

Recursion

=

Function khud ko hi baar-baar call karta hai.

