31. Client-side vs Server-side JavaScript
Client Side	Server Side
Runs in Browser	Runs on Server
Uses Browser	Uses Node.js
Manipulates HTML	Connects Database
Faster UI	Handles Business Logic
Client Side Example
document.body.style.background="red";

Changes webpage.

Server Side Example
const express = require("express");

Creates server.

